    "notes": "- **Ripeness requires a claim to be sufficiently mature for judicial resolution** — not premature or contingent on future events\n- **Timing requirement**: dispute must have advanced beyond speculation; threat of enforcement must be **real and immediate** (not hypothetical)\n- **Two-part test**: (1) fitness of issue for judicial decision, and (2) hardship to parties from withholding review\n- Unripe claims are dismissed for lack of justiciability; burden on **plaintiff to demonstrate ripeness**",
