    "notes": "- **Presumption Against Preemption**: Courts **presume Congress did not intend to preempt state law**, especially in areas of **traditional state concern** (health, safety, family law)\n  – Burden on federal government/preemption proponent to show **clear and manifest** intent to preempt\n\n- **Exceptions** (presumption does NOT apply):\n  – **Regulation of foreign affairs** (uniformity required)\n  – **Interstate/international commerce** (federal uniformity essential)\n  – **Occupation of federal field** (no state role)\n  – Congressional statement of **explicit preemptive intent** (express preemption language)\n\n- When presumption applies: **strict construction** against preemption; state law narrowly saved when possible",
