    "notes": "- **Implied Preemption**: Arises when express clause absent but **federal scheme is so comprehensive** it implicitly displaces state law\n\n- **Triggers for Implied Preemption**:\n  – **Pervasive federal regulation** indicating Congress intended exclusive federal control\n  – **Unique federal interest** (immigration, patent law, currency)\n  – **Actual conflict**: State law **impossible to satisfy** alongside federal requirement\n  – **Obstacle to federal purpose**: State law **frustrates** clear federal objective\n\n- **Burden**: Proponent must demonstrate **congressional intent** through scheme's comprehensiveness or federal/state interests\n\n- **Permissive gap**: State law filling **gaps in federal scheme** generally **NOT preempted** (presumption against preemption applies)",
