    "trigger": "An officer conducting a lawful traffic stop glances into the vehicle and observes drug paraphernalia on the back seat. The officer seizes it without consent or warrant.",
    "notes": "- **Three-prong test** (all must be met):\n  1. **Lawful vantage point**: officer must be in location legally (no trespass/unlawful intrusion)\n  2. **Inadvertent discovery**: incriminating nature must be **immediately apparent** without further search/manipulation\n  3. **Plain view access**: officer must have **lawful right of access** to the object itself\n- **Immediately apparent** ≠ suspicion; requires **probable cause** from plain view alone\n- **Burden on government**: must prove all three elements; failure on any prong defeats seizure\n- **Contrast**: plain view **does not justify further investigation** (e.g., opening containers, moving objects to see underneath)",
