    "notes": "- **Fruits doctrine**: Evidence derived from an initial constitutional violation is excludable as 'fruit' of the poisoned tree\n- **Causation requirement**: The subsequent evidence must be **causally connected** to the original illegal police conduct\n- **Standing requirement**: D must have **Fourth Amendment standing** in the place where the initial illegality occurred to challenge fruit\n- **Applies to**: Derivative evidence (statements, physical evidence, witness testimony) flowing from the initial violation, not just direct fruits",
