    "notes": "- **Good faith exception**: Evidence obtained in **objectively reasonable reliance** on a subsequently invalidated warrant is NOT excludable\n- **Four scenarios** where exception applies: (1) warrant later deemed defective; (2) reliance on binding appellate precedent; (3) reliance on statute later struck down; (4) reliance on clerical court records\n- **Burden on prosecution**: State must show **objectively reasonable reliance**—not subjective good faith\n- **No exception for**: Searches with obvious defects (e.g., facially invalid warrant), reckless or grossly negligent police conduct, or when officer knew warrant was unlawful",
