    "trigger": "A plaintiff offers testimony that the defendant owned a red car, in a case where a red car was used in a hit-and-run. The defendant argues the evidence is irrelevant.",
    "notes": "- **Materiality**: Evidence must tend to prove or disprove a **fact of consequence** to the case (not just any fact).\n- **Probativeness**: Evidence must have **logical tendency** to make the fact more or less probable than without it.\n- Both prongs must be satisfied; **either failure defeats relevance** under Rule 401.\n- Note: Probativeness is a **low bar**—even slight tendency to prove/disprove satisfies it.",
