    "notes": "- **Irrelevant evidence is inadmissible as a matter of law**—no discretion to admit it.\n- Rule 402 creates a **bright-line exclusionary rule**: failure to meet Rule 401 = automatic exclusion.\n- **No balancing or judicial discretion** applies (unlike Rule 403 unfair prejudice balancing).\n- Exception: Evidence may be admissible under **specific statutory authorization** (e.g., rape shield laws).",
