    "notes": "- **Character evidence** (Rule 404(a)): Admissible only under narrow exceptions; tests **general propensity or reputation**\n- **Specific acts** (Rule 404(b)): Evidence of prior conduct may be admissible for **non-propensity purposes**: motive, opportunity, plan, knowledge, identity, absence of mistake\n- **Critical distinction**: Use of prior act to prove character (forbidden) vs. use to prove modus operandi/plan (permitted)\n- **Must not be offered to show propensity**: Court must give **limiting instruction** if risk of propensity inference",
