    "question": "Under FRE 405, how may character be proven when it is admissible under Rule 404?",
    "trigger": "Defendant in assault case wants to prove his peaceful character. Can prosecutor force defendant to prove this through specific prior incidents, or only reputation/opinion?",
    "notes": "- **Method depends on context**:\n  - **Civil cases & non-character-trait crimes**: Character proven by **reputation or opinion only** (no specific acts)\n  - **Criminal defendant's character defense**: **Reputation, opinion, AND specific acts** all permitted\n  - **Character for truthfulness** (impeachment): **Reputation, opinion, AND specific acts** allowed\n- **No propensity cross**: Opposing party cannot cross-examine on specific acts unless character is actually at issue\n- **Declarant foundation**: Witness must have **adequate familiarity** with person/community for reputation testimony",
