    "rule": "Admissibility of Character Evidence (Propensity Bar Framework under Rule 404)",
    "question": "When does a defendant 'open the door' to prosecution character evidence under FRE 404(a)(1)?",
    "trigger": "Defendant testifies about his peaceful nature and introduces character witnesses for peacefulness. Can prosecutor now offer bad character evidence?",
    "notes": "- **Door-opening principle**: Once defendant **introduces character evidence**, prosecution may rebut with **same trait** evidence\n- **Scope limitation**: Prosecution can only offer evidence of **same character trait** defendant put in issue (not other traits)\n- **Limited to rebuttal**: Prosecution **cannot initiate** character evidence; must wait for defendant to raise it first\n- **Applies to reputation/opinion only**: If defendant uses specific acts, prosecution limited to **reputation/opinion rebuttal** (except under Rule 405 exceptions)\n- **Timing matters**: Defendant's character evidence (direct or cross-examination) triggers opportunity; not merely defendant's plea or courtroom demeanor",
