    "notes": "- **Habit**: Regular response to repeated specific situations (semi-automatic, uniform, frequent)\n- **Character**: General moral/ethical disposition (broad, vague, inconsistent application)\n- **Key distinction**: Habit is **specific conduct in response to a particular circumstance**; character is about propensity or disposition\n- **Admissibility**: Habit is **NOT subject to Rule 404(a) ban** on character evidence\n- Rule 406 allows habit/routine practice to prove conduct on a particular occasion **without corroboration required** (unlike character under Rule 405)",
