    "notes": "- **Specificity required**: Evidence must describe **particular, identifiable situations** (not general tendencies)\n- **Frequency requirement**: Conduct must be **regular and repeated** in response to the same stimulus\n- **Semi-automatic response**: The conduct must be performed with **consistent uniformity** (nearly reflexive)\n- **Burden on proponent**: Must establish sufficient **regularity and consistency** through testimony or observation\n- Evidence of a few isolated instances or general \"usually does X\" **fails to meet Rule 406 threshold**",
