    "notes": "- **No corroboration requirement**: Rule 406 allows habit evidence **without corroborating evidence**\n- **Distinction from character**: Character evidence under Rule 405 may require corroboration; habit does **NOT**\n- **Single witness sufficiency**: Testimony of **one person describing a well-established habit** is sufficient\n- **Admissibility standard**: Court may admit if evidence is **sufficient to support a finding** that the person had the habit\n- **Trial court discretion**: Judge determines whether regularity/consistency is proven **to the required threshold** before submission to jury",
