    "notes": "- **Lay opinion allowed when:** testimony is **rationally based on the witness's perception** and **helpful to a clear understanding** of the witness's testimony or a fact of consequence\n- **Not based on scientific, technical, or specialized knowledge** requiring expert qualification\n- Opinion must be **grounded in personal sensory experience** (what the witness saw, heard, felt)\n- Examples: speed, intoxication, emotional state, identity of familiar person, value of personal property\n- **Burden on proponent:** establish lay witness had personal perception and opinion flows from that perception",
