    "notes": "- **Lay opinion:** based on **personal sensory perception** without requiring specialized expertise; common sense conclusions from observation\n- **Expert opinion:** requires **specialized knowledge, training, or experience** in a technical, scientific, or other specialized field (FRE 702)\n- **Gray area:** if witness must apply specialized knowledge to draw opinion, **must qualify as expert** even if lay witness could testify to raw facts\n- Officer's speed calculation likely requires **accident reconstruction expertise** → needs expert qualification under FRE 702, not permitted as lay opinion\n- **Key burden:** proponent must show lay opinion does NOT require specialized knowledge",
