    "notes": "**Ultimate issue rule under FRE 704**:\n- **General rule**: Expert **may** testify to an opinion on an ultimate issue\n- **Exception in criminal cases**: Expert **cannot** state opinion on defendant's **mental state or legal insanity** (FRE 704(b))\n- Expert **can** describe the defendant's mental condition; **cannot** conclude legal conclusion (e.g., \"insane\" under jurisdiction's standard)\n\n**Policy**: Prevents experts from usurping jury's role on ultimate legal questions while allowing helpful technical opinions on facts relevant to ultimate issues.",
