    "notes": "- **Authentication** = requirement that evidence is what proponent claims it is (FRE 901(a))\n- Applies to **all evidence**, especially documents\n- **Proponent's burden** = introduce sufficient evidence that jury could find authentication is satisfied\n- **Standard** = not proof beyond reasonable doubt, but enough for reasonable jury to accept authenticity\n- Failure to authenticate = evidence must be excluded under FRE 902 (self-authenticating exceptions exist but are narrow)",
