    "notes": "- **FRE 1002 mandate** = original or duplicate required to prove content of writing, recording, or photograph\n- **Exception for duplicates** (FRE 1003):\n  - Duplicate **admissible** unless genuine dispute about authenticity exists OR it's unfair to admit duplicate\n  - Photocopy, scan, email copy = duplicates\n- **Originals NOT required** if:\n  - Writing is **collateral** to disputed issues (FRE 1004(4))\n  - **Original lost/destroyed** in good faith (FRE 1004(1))\n  - **Original in opponent's possession** and not produced after notice (FRE 1004(3))\n- **Testimonial proof of contents** = forbidden unless exception applies (triggers Rule 1004)",
