    "trigger": "A husband is subpoenaed to testify about his wife's whereabouts during an alleged crime. The wife objects; the husband does not.",
    "notes": "- **Holder of spousal immunity**: The **non-testifying spouse** (the one NOT on the stand) controls the privilege\n- **Burden shifting**: If the **non-testifying spouse objects**, the testifying spouse **cannot testify** even if willing\n- **Waiver**: Immunity is **waived if the non-testifying spouse fails to object** or **explicitly consents**\n- **Effect of divorce**: Spousal immunity **terminates upon divorce**; it protects only **ongoing marriages**\n- **Exception**: Some jurisdictions recognize **crime-fraud exception** or allow testimony about **communications the spouse made to third parties**",
