    "rule": "Spousal Immunity and Confidential Marital Communications Privileges",
    "question": "What constitutes a 'confidential' marital communication for purposes of the privilege, and who may invoke it?",
    "trigger": "During marriage, a wife tells her husband about a tort claim she plans to bring. Years after divorce, she is deposed and asked about this conversation.",
