    "notes": "- **Admissible as substantive evidence** when:\n  - Witness testifies at trial AND is **subject to cross-examination**\n  - Prior statement is **consistent** with trial testimony\n  - Statement was made **before the alleged motive to fabricate or improper influence** arose\n- **Not admissible** merely to corroborate credibility if made **after** the motive to fabricate existed\n- **FRE 801(d)(1)(B)** — removes from hearsay definition when these conditions met",
