    "trigger": "At trial, a witness denies making a prior statement that contradicts her current testimony. The opposing party offers the prior statement as proof of the facts stated.",
    "notes": "- **Admissible as substantive evidence** when:\n  - Witness testifies at trial AND is **subject to cross-examination** about the statement\n  - Statement is **inconsistent** with current testimony\n  - Statement was made **under oath** at a **prior proceeding or deposition**\n- **If not under oath:** admissible only for **impeachment** (credibility), not for truth\n- **FRE 801(d)(1)(A)** — removes from hearsay definition when oath requirement met",
