    "notes": "- **Admissible as substantive evidence** when:\n  - Witness testifies at trial AND is **subject to cross-examination**\n  - Statement is a **prior identification of a person**\n  - Prior identification made after **perceiving** the person\n- **Examples:** photo array ID, lineup ID, \"that's the guy\" statements\n- **FRE 801(d)(1)(C)** — removes from hearsay definition\n- **No oath requirement** unlike inconsistent statements; **no fabrication timing requirement** unlike consistent statements",
