    "trigger": "Defendant allegedly intimidated a key prosecution witness into not appearing at trial. The witness's prior recorded statement (testimonial) is offered in defendant's absence.",
    "notes": "- **Forfeiture by wrongdoing**: Defendant loses Confrontation Clause protection if he **engaged in wrongdoing that caused witness's unavailability**\n- **Wrongdoing** = misconduct by defendant **designed to prevent/procure witness absence** (intimidation, threats, murder)\n- **Burden on prosecution** (by preponderance): Must prove (1) **wrongdoing occurred**, (2) **defendant committed/acquiesced in it**, (3) **wrong caused unavailability**\n- **Judicial discretion** on sufficiency; **not all bad acts qualify** — must be directed at securing witness silence\n- Forfeiture applies **only to testimonial statements** created with knowledge defendant might use forfeiture tactic",
