    "notes": "- **Present Sense Impression**: Statement must be made **while perceiving the event or immediately thereafter** (near-contemporaneous)\n- **Excited Utterance**: Statement may be made **at any time while declarant remains under stress of excitement** (temporal window is broader)\n- **Key distinction**: PSI requires near-simultaneous narration; EU requires only emotional state at time of statement\n- **Timing burden**: Proponent must establish statement was made during or immediately after perception for PSI; for EU, only the excitement state matters",
