    "trigger": "A hospital seeks to admit nursing notes documenting a patient's vital signs recorded during a routine shift. The hospital custodian testifies the notes were made in the normal course of business.",
    "notes": "- **Five foundational elements required:**\n  - **Made at or near the time** of the event/condition\n  - **By someone with knowledge** of the matter\n  - **Made in the regular course** of a business activity\n  - **As a regular practice** of the business to make such records\n  - **Lack of circumstances** suggesting unreliability\n\n- **Burden:** Proponent must establish all five via testimony (usually custodian or qualified witness)\n\n- **Scope:** Applies to **any regularly conducted activity** (not limited to commercial enterprises)",
