    "rule": "Partition Remedies and Procedural Methods",
    "question": "What is the primary purpose and scope of a partition action in a cotenancy?",
    "trigger": "Three joint tenants own commercial property. One tenant seeks to exit the cotenancy and divide their interests. Another cotenant objects and wants to stay in the property.",
    "notes": "- **Purpose**: Partition action dissolves cotenancy by dividing the property or forcing its sale\n- **Scope**: Available to any cotenant (including those with unequal shares) as a matter of **statutory right**\n- **Core remedy**: Court orders either **in-kind partition** (physical division) or **partition by sale** (forced sale with proceeds distributed)\n- **No waiver by agreement**: Cotenants cannot contractually eliminate partition rights (unless structured as alternative entity)",
    "commonVsModern": "",
    "mastered": false,
    "date": "2026-06-25T21:39:34.870Z"
