    "notes": "- **Timing**: Generally **no statute of limitations**—partition is an equitable action (historical exception to repose)\n- **Estoppel/Waiver**: **Burden on defendant** to prove waiver by: (1) **express agreement**, (2) **unjust enrichment/inequitable conduct**, or (3) **implied waiver through long acquiescence** (rare)\n- **Laches doctrine**: May apply if plaintiff delayed suit and prejudice resulted to other cotenant\n- **Note**: Modern jurisdictions increasingly impose repose periods (e.g., 20+ years); **check local statute**",
