    "subject": "Real Property - Cotenancies",
    "rule": "Partition Remedies and Procedural Methods",
    "question": "How are partition proceeds distributed among cotenants, and what adjustments apply for use/occupancy and improvements?",
    "trigger": "After partition by sale yields $500,000, one cotenant claims credit for 10 years of sole occupancy and $50,000 in improvements while the other was absent.",
    "notes": "- **Base distribution**: Proceeds divided **per cotenant's ownership share** (equal for joint tenants; per fractional interest for tenants in common)\n- **Credits for improvements**: Cotenant who made **valuable improvements** may claim **reimbursement only if improvements increased overall property value** (not personal preference upgrades)\n- **Liability for rents/use value**: Occupying cotenant generally **owes nothing** for reasonable use (absent ouster or accounting agreement)\n- **Carrying costs**: Taxes, mortgages, repairs typically split **pro rata by ownership share** unless modified by court order",
