    "rule": "Nature and Type of Easements and Licenses (Appurtenant vs. In Gross vs. License Distinction)",
    "question": "What is the key functional difference between a license and an easement?",
    "trigger": "O tells A, 'You may park your car in my driveway whenever you want.' O later changes his mind and tells A to stop.",
    "notes": "**License (Revocable):**\n- **Mere permission** to use another's land; creates **no property interest**\n- **Revocable at will** by licensor absent consideration or estoppel\n- **Does not run with the land**; terminates upon licensor's death or sale\n- Licensor may exclude or revoke without legal consequence (absent estoppel)\n\n**Easement (Irrevocable):**\n- Creates a **binding property interest/estate** in land\n- **Not revocable at will**; survives death and sale of servient land\n- Must be created with **formality** (typically in writing under Statute of Frauds)\n- Licensee has legal right to enforce against successors\n\n**Estoppel Exception:** License may become irrevocable if licensor's conduct induces reliance and revocation would cause inequitable hardship (**equitable estoppel**)",
    "commonVsModern": "",
    "mastered": false,
    "date": "2026-06-25T21:40:19.229Z"
