    "trigger": "A buyer sues to force a seller to convey land after the seller breaches a binding purchase agreement.",
    "notes": "- **Specific performance is the default remedy** for breach of real estate contracts\n- Rationale: **Land is unique**; damages are inadequate because each parcel is considered irreplaceable\n- Applies to **both buyer and seller** as plaintiff\n- Court has **discretion**; equitable factors apply (unclean hands, laches, hardship to defendant)\n- **Exception**: Specific performance may be denied if enforcement would be inequitable or unduly burdensome",
