    "notes": "- **Part performance** excuses the Statute of Frauds requirement for an oral real estate contract\n- **Acts that satisfy part performance**: (1) **possession by buyer** + (2) **payment of purchase price** AND/OR (3) **substantial improvements** to the property\n- **Possession alone** is insufficient in most jurisdictions; typically need payment + possession or improvements\n- **Burden**: Buyer must prove part performance by **clear and convincing evidence**\n- **Modern trend**: Some jurisdictions reject part performance; rely on equitable estoppel instead",
