    "notes": "- **Damages measure**: **Difference between contract price and market value** at breach (benefit-of-the-bargain rule)\n- **Seller's damages** = Market value − Contract price (if market rose)\n- **Buyer's damages** = Contract price − Market value (if market fell)\n- **Incidental costs** (inspection, appraisal, broker fees) may be recoverable\n- **Consequential damages** are **generally excluded** unless foreseeable and not speculative\n- **Mitigation duty**: Non-breaching party must **take reasonable steps to mitigate loss** (e.g., resell promptly)",
