    "question": "What conduct constitutes a violation of the diligence duty under MRPC 1.3?",
    "trigger": "A lawyer takes two weeks to respond to opposing counsel's discovery requests, misses a court deadline by one day, and neglects to calendar important dates.",
    "notes": "- **Violations include**: Unjustified delay in filing pleadings, responding to court orders, or advancing client matters\n- **Neglect of deadlines** (court-imposed or contractual) = clear breach\n- **Failure to communicate** progress to client on material developments\n- **Abandonment** of representation without notice or substitute counsel\n- **Pattern of inattention** evidences lack of diligence (not isolated mistakes)",
