    "trigger": "A client in writing asks their lawyer to handle the matter 'whenever you get around to it' and explicitly waives strict timelines for document review.",
    "notes": "- Client **cannot waive** certain time-critical obligations (court-imposed deadlines, statute of limitations)\n- Client **may waive or modify** diligence standards for matter-specific delays with **informed consent in writing**\n- **Burden on lawyer**: Must obtain explicit waiver before deferring work beyond reasonable norms\n- Waiver does **not excuse abandonment** or gross negligence\n- **Competing client matters** do not excuse delay without client knowledge and consent",
