    "trigger": "A lawyer fails to update a client for six months on case progress, though discovery work continues in the background.",
    "notes": "- Diligence duty **intersects with communication duty** (MRPC 1.4)\n- **Lack of diligence** often manifested through **failure to communicate** status updates\n- Lawyer must keep client **reasonably informed** of case developments and deadlines\n- **Burden on lawyer**: Regular updates satisfy both diligence and communication obligations\n- Silence or unresponsiveness = evidence of breach under MRPC 1.3 **even if work proceeds**",
