    "subject": "Professional Responsibility - Communications",
    "rule": "MRPC Rule 1.4: Duties to keep the client reasonably informed, consult about means, promptly comply with reasonable requests for information, and explain matters to permit informed decisions.",
    "question": "What does MRPC 1.4(a)(2) require a lawyer to do regarding the means by which a matter will be handled?",
    "trigger": "A family law client wants aggressive litigation tactics, but the lawyer believes mediation would be faster and cheaper. The lawyer hasn't discussed alternative approaches.",
    "notes": "- **Core duty:** **Consult with the client about the means by which the objectives of the representation will be accomplished**\n- **Key trigger:** Significant strategic or tactical decisions—not routine administrative choices\n- **Burden on lawyer:** Proactively raise available options (litigation, settlement, mediation, ADR)\n- **Client decision-making:** Consultation enables **informed consent** to the chosen approach",
