    "trigger": "A lawyer settles a case without telling the client about a significant development that occurred the day before settlement negotiations began.",
    "notes": "- **Core duty:** Keep client **reasonably informed** about the status and material developments of the representation\n- **Standard:** Reasonableness balances frequency and detail based on client's needs and sophistication\n- **Material developments:** Settlement offers, adverse rulings, opposing party demands, missed deadlines\n- **Burden on lawyer:** Proactive communication—waiting for client to ask is insufficient",
