    "question": "What are the mandatory elements a lawyer must establish before obtaining informed consent to waive a concurrent-client conflict under MRPC 1.7(b)?",
    "trigger": "A lawyer represents both spouses in estate planning but later discovers their wills contain divergent provisions that may require different legal strategies.",
    "notes": "**MRPC 1.7(b) permits waiver ONLY if:**\n- **Lawyer reasonably believes** she can provide competent, diligent representation to each client\n- **Lawyer reasonably believes** representation will not adversely affect loyalty to either client\n- **Informed written consent** from each affected client (must be in writing and explain conflict)\n- **Each client must have opportunity to seek independent counsel** — not merely offered, but client must have genuine option\n- **Consent must be knowing and voluntary** — no pressure, duress, or inadequate disclosure\n- **Burden is on the lawyer** to affirmatively establish each element before proceeding",
