    "rule": "MRPC Rule 3.1: Requirement that claims and contentions have a basis in law and fact and are not frivolous, including good-faith arguments for extension, modification, or reversal of existing law.",
    "question": "What is the temporal scope of MRPC 3.1's requirement—when must a lawyer ensure claims have a basis in law and fact?",
    "trigger": "A lawyer files a motion to dismiss, but during discovery realizes the factual allegations lack any evidentiary support. She asks whether she must amend or withdraw.",
    "notes": "- **Timing**: 3.1 applies **before AND during proceedings**\n- **Before filing**: Lawyer must conduct reasonable factual/legal investigation\n- **During proceedings**: Lawyer must **promptly withdraw or amend** if later discovers claim is frivolous\n- Burden shifts to **withdrawal/correction** once claim becomes unsupportable\n- Failure to withdraw = continued violation of 3.1\n- Does NOT require lawyer to concede opponent's position, only to abandon truly frivolous ones",
