    "notes": "- **False statements of material fact or law** are prohibited\n- Statement must be **knowingly** false (actual knowledge required)\n- Applies to statements made **to third persons** (opposing parties, insurers, courts, witnesses)\n- **Materiality test**: Would the fact/law likely influence the third person's decision or conduct?\n- Does NOT require intent to defraud—only that lawyer knew statement was false",
